 genetic variation for Pinus ponderosa in the Inland Northwest (USA): applications in gene resource management (1991) Can. J. For. Res., 21, pp. 1491-1500; Rehfeldt, G.E., Genetic variation in the Ponderosae of the southwest (1993) Am. J. Bot., 80, pp. 330-343; Rehfeldt, G.E., Adaptation of Picea engelmannii populations to the heterogeneous environments of the Intermountain West (1994) Can. J. Bot., 72, pp. 1197-1208; Rehfeldt, G.E., Tchebakova, N.M., Barnhardt, L.K., Efficacy of climate transfer functions: introduction of Eurasian populations of Larix into Alberta (1999) Can. J. For. Res., 29, pp. 1660-1668; Rehfeldt, G.E., Ying, C.C., Spittlehouse, D.L., Hamilton Jr., D.A., Genetic responses to climate in Pinus contorta: niche breath, climate change, and reforestation (1999) Ecol. Monogr., 69, pp. 375-407; Rehfeldt, G.E., Tchebakova, N.M., Milyutin, L.I., Parfenova, E.I., Wykoff, W.R., Kouzmina, N.A., Assessing population responses to climate in Pinus sylvestris and Larix spp. of Eurasia with climate-transfer models (2003) Eurasian J. Forestry, 6, pp. 83-98; Rehfeldt, G.E., Tchebakova, N.M., Parfenova, E., Genetic responses to climate and climate change in conifers of the temperate and boreal forests (2004) Recent Res. Dev. Genet. Breeding, 1, pp. 113-130; Rice, K.J., Emery, N.C., Managing microevolution: restoration in the face of global change (2003) Ecol. Environ., 1, pp. 469-478; Sáenz-Romero, C., Snively, A., Lindig-Cisneros, R., Conservation and restoration of pine forest genetic resources in Mexico (2003) Silvae Genetica, 52, pp. 233-237; Sáenz-Romero, C., Tapia-Olivares, B.L., Pinus oocarpa isoenzymatic variation along an altitudinal gradient in Michoacán, Mexico (2003) Silvae Genetica, 52, pp. 237-240; Sáenz-Romero, C., Lindig-Cisneros, R., Evaluación y propuestas para el programa de reforestación en Michoacán, Mexico (2004) Ciencia Nicolaíta, 37, pp. 107-122; SAS Institute, (1988) SAS/STAT User's Guide; Release 6.03 Edition, , SAS Institute, Cary, NC; Sh